{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"traumatic-homicidal-turkey","description":"## Summary\n\nThe `langfuse tracing round-trip (ephemeral self-hosted)` job of the `external-integration`\nworkflow has been broken since the d6d1 cutover (2026-06-22) and tests behavior that no\nlonger exists. Two independent breakages:\n\n1. **Readiness probe imports an uninstalled SDK.** `.github/workflows/external-integration.yml:128`\n   runs `from langfuse import get_client; assert get_client().auth_check()`, but the `langfuse`\n   Python SDK was dropped from `[agents]` in c282b2950. `pip install -e '.[dev]'` no longer\n   installs it, so all 24 readiness iterations raise `ModuleNotFoundError` — hidden by\n   `2>/dev/null`, masquerading as \"Langfuse project did not initialize in time\".\n\n2. **Test asserts a removed trace_id round-trip.** `tests/external/test_llm_trace.py:100` asserts\n   `result[\"trace_id\"]` is truthy and fetches `GET /api/public/traces/{id}`. The runner now\n   hardcodes `trace_id=None` (src/rebar/llm/runner.py:391); the SDK trace-id capture was deleted\n   in 2e9bd4205 when tracing became write-only OTLP export (src/rebar/llm/tracing.py). Also the\n   job never installs `[tracing]`, so `setup_tracing` no-ops and no spans are exported at all.\n\n## Decision (user, 2026-07-09)\n\nRewrite the job to validate CURRENT behavior (write-only OTLP span export to Langfuse), not the\nremoved SDK trace_id round-trip.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Trigger the `external-integration` workflow (langfuse-trace job).\n2. Observe \"Wait for Langfuse to be ready\" time out after 120s (\"project did not initialize in time\").\n\nExpected: readiness passes; a review run's OTLP spans land in Langfuse and the test confirms it.\nActual: readiness fails on a hidden ModuleNotFoundError; the test would fail on the None trace_id anyway.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Readiness probe no longer imports the langfuse SDK; uses a REST check (e.g. `curl -fsS -u pk:sk .../api/public/projects`) and does not mask stderr.\n- [ ] The langfuse-trace job installs the `[tracing]` extra so OTLP export actually fires.\n- [ ] `tests/external/test_llm_trace.py` asserts OTLP spans for a review run are ingested by Langfuse (fetched via REST), with no reliance on a runner-surfaced `trace_id`.\n- [ ] Verified end-to-end: the rewritten test passes against the docker-compose.langfuse.yml stack with a real review call, and the external-integration GitHub Action's langfuse-trace job runs successfully.","id":"416d-c02a-5be4-46ad","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"langfuse-trace job tests removed behavior + readiness probe imports uninstalled SDK"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783647648657501001,"uuid":"0466e440-6723-498e-878f-98dc0ed7b382"}